<div class="container-fluid">

<a href="https://huguesjohnson.com/aridia/">
<div class="container-fluid">
	<div class="clearfix">
		<img class="float-start" src="https://www.huguesjohnson.com/images/feature-nav/aridia.jpg" alt="Aridia"/>
		<p><b>Aridia</b></p>
<p>Aridia is a rom editor for Phantasy Star III. It has a mostly-friendly interface that makes editing incredibly easy. No messing with hex editors, decoding values, or any of that. If you can click and type then you can hack away to your heart's contentment.</p>
	</div>
</div>
</a>
<br>

<a href="https://huguesjohnson.com/eisfrei/">
<div class="container-fluid">
	<div class="clearfix">
		<img class="float-start" src="https://www.huguesjohnson.com/images/feature-nav/eisfrei.jpg" alt="Eisfrei"/>
		<p><b>Eisfrei</b></p>
<p>Eisfrei is a ROM editor for Herzog Zwei that allows editing of text, unit attributes, order attributes, and tile-based graphics.</p>
	</div>
</div>
</a>
<br>

<a href="https://huguesjohnson.com/hapsby.html">
<div class="container-fluid">
	<div class="clearfix">
		<img class="float-start" src="https://www.huguesjohnson.com/images/feature-nav/hapsby.jpg" alt="Hapsby"/>
		<p><b>Hapsby</b></p>
<p>Hapsby is a save state/save game editor for Java compatible platforms. It currently supports over 30 games, adding support for new games is relatively uncomplicated.</p>
	</div>
</div>
</a>
<br>

<a href="https://huguesjohnson.com/guides/ys5-save-state-hacking/">
<div class="container-fluid">
	<div class="clearfix">
		<img class="float-start" src="https://www.huguesjohnson.com/images/feature-nav/ys-v-save-state-hacking.png" alt="Ys V Save State Hacking"/>
		<p><b>Ys V Save State Hacking</b></p>
<p>A small guide on how to hack HP, MP, XP, and items in Ys V save states.</p>
	</div>
</div>
</a>
<br>

<a href="https://huguesjohnson.com/guides/cf2-sram/">
<div class="container-fluid">
	<div class="clearfix">
		<img class="float-start" src="https://www.huguesjohnson.com/images/feature-nav/cf2sram.png" alt="Hacking Cosmic Fantasy 2 save RAM out of spite"/>
		<p><b>Hacking Cosmic Fantasy 2 save RAM out of spite</b></p>
<p>An occasionally long winded piece that eventually explains how to edit character statistics &amp; inventory in Cosmic Fantasy 2.</p>
	</div>
</div>
</a>
<br>



<a href="https://huguesjohnson.com/power-ups/">
<div class="container-fluid">
	<div class="clearfix">
		<img class="float-start" src="https://www.huguesjohnson.com/images/feature-nav/power-ups.jpg" alt="Power-Ups"/>
		<p><b>Power-Ups</b></p>
<p>Power-Ups are a collection of single-game save state editors and cheating utilities. They're each designed to edit a single aspect from a specific game. They're things that are too complicated to fit into Hapsby but not something I want to devote a huge Aridia-like effort to.</p>
	</div>
</div>
</a>
<br>

